-------> Stewardship: Properties of money

Last week in stewardship we covered the health topic of food. 

The summary of that is eat what God made and give thanks for the food when you consume it. Fruit roll ups are not made by God. 

If it walks around, swims or grows out of soil, God made it for us as food. Beware of eating products made by man that are called food. Many are poisons. Counterfeit foods


This week we’re covering money and the topic is properties of money. 

Discernment of good vs bad money is important for wise stewardship of your time

Sounds boring and it’s very simple but also super important

Important, because if you don’t understand the properties of money, you might unintentionally and unknowingly saving your time (that’s what money is) in a currency that steals from you and others. 

A sinful system of theft at a mass scale through counterfeiting known as inflation.

Proverbs 11:1 says that a false balance is an abomination to the Lord but a just weight is his delight.

The Lord delights in honest measures. Money is a measure. Fiat is dishonest currency, a form of money. Bitcoin is honest money and can also be used as currency


7 properties of Money


Scarcity - Fiat bad, gold better because it only inflates around 2% per year right now, Bitcoin best because it has a fixed supply 
Portability - bring it with you
Acceptability - ability to spend it. Fiat good
Divisibilty - divide and aggregate. Gold bad
Uniformity/ fungibility - are units interchangeable?
Durability - does it resist decay?. Apples
Securability - How easily can you protect it?

Use fiat, gold and bitcoin as examples 

Theft is wrong
Counterfeiting is theft
Inflation is counterfeiting

Inflation of a currency by a select few is immoral and fraudulent. Inflation is stealing and God said we should not steal

Stealing is a sin


